            <title>[CASSANDRA-7228] Closing CqlRecordReader doesn&apos;t release all resources</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-7228</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Closing CqlRecordReader doesn&apos;t release all resources - only session object is closed, cluster remains open. It may result in &quot;too many open files&quot; error, caused by still open cassandra connections (I had this error while working on my own InputFormat for cassandra  - &lt;a href=&quot;https://bitbucket.org/mrk/cassandra_hadoop_utils/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://bitbucket.org/mrk/cassandra_hadoop_utils/&lt;/a&gt;). Attached patch fixes this issue for me.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
